Drop the docs subdir from the build.

gdm's docs/meson.build calls gnome.yelp(), which unconditionally requires the
itstool program (and the yelp help toolchain) with no meson option to disable
it. The yelp help pages are irrelevant to our headless server/QEMU target, so
we remove the subdir rather than pull in itstool. The Gdm-1.0 typelib and the
daemon/greeter are unaffected.

--- a/meson.build
+++ b/meson.build
@@ -343,7 +343,6 @@ if have_xdmcp
   subdir('chooser')
 endif
-subdir('docs')

 gnome.post_install(
   glib_compile_schemas: true,
